Scientists had a new idea. They made a robot arm from plants. They used cotton. The arm is soft and strong. It works very well.

The scientists put the robot arm in the ground. It disappeared in eight weeks. It became part of the soil. 

These new robots are safe for nature. They might help doctors too. But scientists must do more work first. They need to make better power parts.', 'published', '2025-12-17 07:45:11.140677', '2025-12-17 07:32:39.709651');
INSERT INTO public.versions (id, article_id, level, title, content, source, syllabus_coverage, library_tags, stages, value_tags, grading_data, original_content, status, published_at, created_at) VALUES (10, 4, 'L1', '', 'Robots are usually stronger than humans, but they create a big problem. Old robots become trash that stays on Earth for a long time. This is called e-waste. What if robots could break down and disappear like plants?

Wei and Zhang are two researchers who wanted to solve this. They decided to build a robot using natural materials. They started with cellulose from cotton. They mixed it with a liquid called glycerol. This created a new material that was soft but strong.

They built a robot arm and a controller with this special material. After testing the parts, they buried them in the soil. In just eight weeks, the parts disappeared. They completely broke down in the dirt.

Wei and Zhang hope these robots can help people in the future. For example, doctors could use them inside the human body to help with surgery. Then, the robot would safely disappear inside the patient. However, the technology is still new. Scientists say that the electronic parts inside the robots are not biodegradable yet. We still need to find a way to make the whole robot disappear, not just the arm.', 'AI生成', '{"junior": {"coverage": 0.69, "stage_matches": {"stage1": {"stage_name": "\u7834\u51b0\u671f (Novice)", "filters": {"level": {"passed": false, "expected": ["L0"], "actual": "L1"}}, "match": false, "reason": "Level\u4e0d\u5339\u914d"}, "stage2": {"stage_name": "\u8fdb\u9636\u671f (Intermediate)", "filters": {"level": {"passed": true, "expected": ["L0", "L1"], "actual": "L1"}, "genre": {"passed": true}, "topic": {"passed": false}}, "match": false, "reason": "\u9898\u6750\u4e0d\u5339\u914d"}, "stage3": {"stage_name": "\u7a81\u7834\u671f (Advanced)", "filters": {"level": {"passed": true, "expected": ["L1", "L2"], "actual": "L1"}, "genre": {"passed": true}, "topic": {"passed": false}}, "match": false, "reason": "\u9898\u6750\u4e0d\u5339\u914d"}, "stage4": {"stage_name": "\u51b2\u523a\u671f (Elite)", "filters": {"level": {"passed": false, "expected": ["L2", "L3"], "actual": "L1"}}, "match": false, "reason": "Level\u4e0d\u5339\u914d"}}}, "senior": {"coverage": 0.7, "stage_matches": {"stage1": {"stage_name": "\u7b51\u57fa\u671f", "filters": {"level": {"passed": true, "expected": ["L0", "L1"], "actual": "L1"}, "genre": {"passed": true}, "topic": {"passed": false}}, "match": false, "reason": "\u9898\u6750\u4e0d\u5339\u914d"}, "stage2": {"stage_name": "\u722c\u5761\u671f", "filters": {"level": {"passed": true, "expected": ["L1", "L2"], "actual": "L1"}, "genre": {"passed": true}, "topic": {"passed": false}}, "match": false, "reason": "\u9898\u6750\u4e0d\u5339\u914d"}, "stage3": {"stage_name": "\u653b\u575a\u671f", "filters": {"level": {"passed": false, "expected": ["L2"], "actual": "L1"}}, "match": false, "reason": "Level\u4e0d\u5339\u914d"}, "stage4": {"stage_name": "\u9738\u699c\u671f", "filters": {"level": {"passed": false, "expected": ["L3"], "actual": "L1"}}, "match": false, "reason": "Level\u4e0d\u5339\u914d"}}}}', '["junior_stage2", "senior_stage1", "junior_stage1", "senior_stage2"]', '{"junior": [], "senior": []}', '{"junior": [], "senior": []}', '{"level": "L1", "level_name": "\u8fdb\u9636\u8fc7\u6e21 (Level 1)", "tags": {"genre": "Expository", "genre_sub": "Science", "domain": "Man & Nature", "topic_sub": "Ecology"}, "dimensions": {"vocab_profile": {"ngsl_coverage": 0.766, "nawl_ratio": 0.096, "level": "L3"}, "avg_sentence_length": {"value": 10.0, "level": "L1"}, "fkgl_score": {"value": 5.6, "level": "L1"}, "complex_sentence_density": {"value": 0.368, "count": 7, "level": "L2"}, "word_count": {"value": 190, "level": "L1"}}}', 'Robots are usually stronger than humans, but they create a big problem. Old robots become trash that stays on Earth for a long time. This is called e-waste. What if robots could break down and disappear like plants?

Wei and Zhang are two researchers who wanted to solve this. They decided to build a robot using natural materials. They started with cellulose from cotton. They mixed it with a liquid called glycerol. This created a new material that was soft but strong.

